<title>JAPAN: Asahi Bank reveals problem loans.</title>
<headline>Asahi Bank reveals problem loans.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Asahi Bank Ltd has disclosed</p>
<p>its restructured loans (in billions of yen unless specified):</p>
<p>					end-Mar 97     end-Mar 96</p>
<p>  Restructured loans	    138.1	    345.0</p>
<p>  Bad loans			 190.0	    145.2</p>
<p>  Non-performing loans	  296.0	    292.6</p>
<p>  Loans to troubled clients   104.6	    423.2</p>
<p>  Total problem loans	   728.7	     1.21 trln</p>
<p>Restructured loans are those on which interest rates have been cut to help corporate restructuring. Bad loans are to bankrupt firms and non-performing are those with interest payments in arrears by six months or more. Loans to troubled clients are mainly to the bank's non-bank affiliates.</p>
</text>
